text:
the violence against women's act (vawa) also allowed for undocumented survivors to be able to come forward and make reports without fear of deportation. 
vawa crosses across many movements. women need wava, undocumented survivors need vawa, trans survivors need vawa, children need vawa, male survivors also need vawa.

allowing wava to expires sends a clear message - the same message this administration has sent since its campaign, fueled by elected representatives with the same agenda. that message is we don't matter. .
.

text:
[kilas balik 16 film festival bali 2018]

1 desember 2018.

opening night diadakan di uma seminyak (@umaseminyak) pukul 17:00 wita. ada beberapa kegiatan yang dilakukan pada hari tersebut, yaitu pemutaran film, sesi #hearmetoo dan penampilan puisi visual.

kegiatan diawali dengan pemutaran film "posesif" (2017) karya edwin. kemudian dilanjutkan dengan #hearmetoo session dengan tema "kekerasan dalam pacaran dari sisi kesehatan mental dan hukum" bersama @candramertha (pengacara publik ylbhi-lbh bali), @dokteraidotcom dan penyintas kekerasan dalam pacaran. kegiatan ditutup dengan penampilan puisi visual oleh @liberal.literasi dengan judul "si puan".
.
@gshrudayana @kisara_bali @lbh_bali

name: GSHR Udayana
tweet_full:
[kilas balik 16 film festival bali 2018]

1 desember 2018.

opening night diadakan di uma seminyak (@umaseminyak) pukul 17:00 wita. ada beberapa kegiatan yang dilakukan pada hari tersebut, yaitu pemutaran film, sesi #hearmetoo dan penampilan puisi visual.

kegiatan diawali dengan pemutaran film "posesif" (2017) karya edwin. kemudian dilanjutkan dengan #hearmetoo session dengan tema "kekerasan dalam pacaran dari sisi kesehatan mental dan hukum" bersama @candramertha (pengacara publik ylbhi-lbh bali), @dokteraidotcom dan penyintas kekerasan dalam pacaran. kegiatan ditutup dengan penampilan puisi visual oleh @liberal.literasi dengan judul "si puan".
.
@gshrudayana @kisara_bali @lbh_bali

#gshrudayana #genderstudies #sexualitystudies #humanrightsstudies #bali #hearmetoo #metoo #gerakbersama #hapuskekerasanseksual #enambelasffest #enambelasffestbali

text: being a woman in northeastern nc is being a 2nd class citizen. there was barely a civil rights movement here and no womenâ€™s movement ever. organized religion and societal expectations serve to keep women silent and in their places. even professional, educated ones. today i was asked to collaborate on a film about rural women in eastern nc. finally! humbled and so very thankful. photo credit f. roy johnson. 1940s. #ahoskienc #hertfordcountync #rural #women #womenofcolor #easternnc #intersectionalfeminism #womanism #metoo

text:
let's talk abuse awareness!  sometimes i hear people say: "i don't understand how you can be so naive having experienced so many cruel things in your life." . 
the thing is, i am not naive, i do understand what is happening around me.
. 
but i've been so angry and bitter before. if i did not believe in the good of mankind. if i did not believe that your strength is to be found in your ability to show kindness. i would not have been able to let go of all the hatred i once felt towards others and myself. i would not have dared to be vulnerable
. 
i accept being hurt from time to time by giving people the benefits of my doubts.  this because i truly feel and think that  the happiness i find one good person is worth ten times the anger
one person can generate.
. 
this is something i've learned the hard way.
. 
i'm not naive. i've lived. i've chosen to be open to new friendships and new experiences. why? because i have experienced so much darkness
.
.
.

text_retweet:
anthonia alasa-ojenagbon is a sexual abuse survivor. underneath her positive, never-say-die outlook on life lies a little girl whose innocence was taken away by someone she trusted.

thank you anthonia for speaking your truth.

#repost @toniabruisedbutnotbroken

a bishop sent me a message saying l should stop taking about sexual violence since god has helped me,now l am married(in his words) he went as far as advising me  not to bring shame on the man who married me. in his words the man did me a great favor. 
this is my response, sir with all due respect l will not stop talking. i will continue to lend my voice ,l will continue to speak out  against rape ,molestation,incest or any form of sexual violence until something is done. i am a christian girl who is not ashamed to speak out. 
our dear ochanya died after being violated sexually for years by father and son ğŸ˜­ğŸ˜­ and some people still think talking about this does not make sense? how many more innocent children will die before we know there is an emergency? most sexual violence cases are perpetrated by people the victims know. because of society's shame,stigma and judgement most survivors never speak. the number of survivors who have spoken is nothing compared to the ones who have never spoken about their abuse. we will not keep quiet. 
sexual violence can have harmful and lasting consequences for the victims,families, communities.  sexual violence victimisation is associated with several health risk behaviour. the effects can have psychological,emotional,and physical effects on a survivor. the effects are not easy to deal,it can take a life time to heal. with the right help and support survivors can be managed.

sexual violence is not a joke,it should never be trivialised.  we will not be silenced. our voice,our power.... to everyone who has survived, l salute you big time. i salute your courage. i salute your strength. we survived the abuse,we will definitely survive the recovery . our lives matter. 
#metoomovement #metoo #notoviolenceagainstwomen #nigerianfeminist #irememberabuse #unmutted #awakening #nomore

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
what happens when things don't go according to plan? 
over the last four weeks i've been working with women in the uk and abroad on a project that explores female sexuality and pleasure. each woman was given a disposable camera to start a dialogue about this still frequently taboo topic and take photos of their interpretation.

nevertheless, all cameras turned out like this..... fml
vdm
qmd

text:
#women that made my #2018.

le #donne del 2018.

1. @jacindaardern , attuale primo ministro della nuova zelanda e leader del partito laburista, mentre allatta la sua figlia in seduta parlamentare com accanto il marito. 
2. #frances hamilton arnold, biochimica e ingegneria statunitense, premio nobel @nobelprize_org per la chimica del 2018, "per i loro lavori su enzimi, peptidi e anticorpi" contributo per la cura cancro. nel 2005 le Ã¨ stato diagnosticato un cancro al seno, che ha sconfitto.

3. il #g7, la #merkel e la classe. no comment! 
4. margherita #pagani, ceo di #impacton @impactonorg , un network che consente di conoscere e diffondere le idee a impatto sociale migliori. scopre come i modelli che funzionano devono poter essere applicati a livello locale. parte dall'esempio dei rifugiati di #idromeni, in grecia. 
5. letizia @letiziabattaglia_anthologia (palermo, 5 marzo 1935) Ã¨
"la fotografa della mafia". le sue foto, spesso in un vivido e nitido bianco e nero, si prefiggono di raccontare soprattutto palermo nella sua miseria e nel suo splendore, i suoi morti di mafia ma anche le sue tradizioni, gli sguardi di bambini e donne. 
6. il movimento #metoo Ã¨ un movimento di matrice femminista che verte contro le molestie e la violenza sulle donne. nel 2018, non solo le donne parlano delle loro esperienze ma gli autori dei reati sono chiamati a rendere conto delle loro azioni.

#buonanno, #donne, #2018, #woman #power, #speakout, #consigli, #coscienza #storia

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. heâ€™s the only straight man iâ€™ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. heâ€™s the only straight man iâ€™ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. heâ€™s the only straight man iâ€™ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
as we continue to review the highlights of 2018, we are awed by the courage and tenacity of nadia murad.  ms. murad was awarded the 2018 nobel peace prize (with denis mukwege) and is the witness who tells of the abuses perpetrated against herself and others. she has shown uncommon courage in recounting her own sufferings and speaking up on behalf of other victims. 
an excerpt of her nobel lecture "let us all unite to fight injustice and oppression; let us raise our voices together and say: no to violence, yes to peace, no to slavery, yes to freedom, no to racial discrimination, yes to equality and to human rights for all.
no to exploiting women and children, yes to providing a decent and independent life to them, no to impunity for criminals, yes to holding criminals accountable and to achieving justice." (nobel acceptance lecture)

text: throughout this entire process, i felt like i've had no control. even when i'm given control in the reporting process at my school, in therapy, in how i tell my story to you, it doesn't feel like control: it feels like a train with no tracks. i have no idea what i'm doing, i have no idea what i need, i don't even know what i am capable of doing. i don't know the rules i'm supposed to follow or what everything is supposed to look like. but that's the thing about sexual assault and recovery-- there is no textbook case. there isn't one way to do it. each storm is a little different, but that doesn't mean we can't learn how to navigate the water amid the turmoil. that's where the control is: i get to decide what my goals are for reporting, what changes i want to see in my life and mental health, and how my story is told. i get to make my own tracks. i may not have had control over what happened to me, but i get to decide where i go from here. and that is incredibly comforting #comfort #confidence #control #rules #oceanside #ocean #sailing #recovery #inspiration #motivation #instaquote #instagood #mylife #mythoughts #writersofinstagram #positivevibes #thoughts #learning #learn #poetrycommunity #writing #thoughts #thoughtoftheday #positivequotes #positivity #positivethinking #mylife #me #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #metoo #anxiety
name: Carmen Hernandez

text:
what even is healing anyway? â¡ï¸please swipe to read about my perceptions of healingâ¡ï¸
(sorry this is like super long, i just wanted to be real with you all)
throughout the past year since i was raped, i have defined healing in many ways in a desperate attempt to feel like i have "solved the problem" of my ptsd, anxiety, depression, flashbacks and nightmares. i wanted to feel in control. i wanted to feel like i could "fix" myself. but truthfully, there is no "fixing" trauma. all of these perceptions of healings left me feeling  just as broken. i am not fully sure what healing will look like for me. but i'm not sure if i believe it will ever be something that feels like it can be completed.

text:
carmen maria machado
author
â€”
i finally read carmen maria machado's collection of short stories, "her body and other parties" over the holiday, and it knocked my head clean off. each story is a haunting chronicle of the way women have learned to inhabit physical bodies in this patriarchal world. carmen's stories are metaphysical in a way that feels so natural. they feel like equal parts science fiction, and science fact - just like a female body often does. pick up this book, and devour it when the time is right. (pro tip: brush up on your law & order)
.
from @vulture - as the world began to pay attention to womenâ€™s stories of abuse, her queer, liminal stories held a flickering candle to the subtle forms of cruelty that continue to go undiscussed.
.
it is impossible to know how machadoâ€™s stories would have been received in another era, but in this one, they have reverberated among readers with the prophetic force of a soothsayerâ€™s divinations. â€œthe way she arcs so gracefully from gothic romance to comedy to horror, feels true to me of how we live our lives,â€ the author karen russell, a fan, told me in an email. â€œa life story is multi-genre, and in the course of a day your love story might turn into a horror story, or vice versa.â€
.
machadoâ€™s fiction is richest when it delves into those internal, haunting moments that mark a womanâ€™s life. as russell put it, her work shows â€œhow the violence migrates inward, from the wider culture into womenâ€™s private minds and bodies. itâ€™s wonderful that we have these stories in the era of metoo, when there is a need and an appetite for the truths that only fiction can tell,â€ russell added.
.

text:
this year has taught me a lot. a. lot. thank you everyone who has contributed to my positive growth, you know who you are... everything that happened also inspired me to be stronger and stand up for what i truly believe in.
more power to all the people who shared their #metoo experiences. 
more strength to those who are fighting the system, everyday. 
2019 has no room for casual sexism and  patriarchal bs and it's about time people get their act right, for there will be consequences. 
this new year let us do our bit, let's start with being sensitive and making the world more inclusive. i am determined and won't back down. join the team
.
.
.
 #ateam #genderequality #feminism #feminist #progress #healtheworld #positivevibes #smashthepatriarchy
.
.
.

text:
2018 akan segera berakhir dan seperti biasanya industri hiburan akan disibukkan dengan akhir tahun.

disaat ada banyak selebriti yang suksesn adapula beberapa yang terlibat dalam kontroversi dan menjatuhkan reputasi mereka. selama satu tahun ini, media sports today menyiapkan penghargaan 2018 dengan opini yang subjektif. 
berikut adalah selebriti yang terpilih menjadi "the worst person of the year". .
1. yang hyun suk: pembatalan debut 'mixnine'
"dengan kekuatan yg sebagai tiang, dia mengatakan akan mendebutkan dan menempatkan trainee dalam kompetisi. namun ia membatalkan debut mereka karena program itu gagal. dia menciptakan kontroversi dengan menanggapinya dengan mengambil tindakan hukum lewat gugatan balik. kemudian bahkan setahun kemudian, ia menciptakan acara audisi yang sama 'yg treasure box.' ide ironisnya mengejutkan semua orang. " - reporter yoon hye young.

2. lee seo won: pelecehan seksual
"tingkah lakunya yang berani setelah pelecehan seksual, ketidaktahuan terus-menerus, dan terakhir, tindakannya melarikan diri ke militer. aku terkejut 3 kali." - reporter kim sat byul

3. kim saeng min: #metoo
"dia menghabiskan waktu emas yang ditunggu-tunggu dalam 25 tahun. kau mendapatkan apa yang kamu berikan." - reporter kim na yeon

4. nancy lang x wang: pernikahan dan perceraian yang kontroversial
"pembuat masalah dengan perkawinan, perkelahian, dan perceraian yang gaduh." - reporter han ye ji

5  lee jin min cp: manipulasi 'heart signal 2' "dia menciptakan program viral 'heart signal' tetapi ada juga banyak kontroversi. dia bahkan lebih mengecewakan penonton dengan perilakunya yang tidak menyenangkan dalam wawancara tentang kesalahan siaran, manipulasi dalam penyuntingan, dan banyak lagi." - reporter moon soo yeon

6. microdot: penipuan orang tua
"orang tuanya berbohong kepada orang-orang di kota mereka, putranya berbohong kepada pemirsa." - reporter kim hyun min

bagaimana menurut kalian?
.

text:
2018.... it was the year of #metoo, pay equity, and our prime minister becoming a mum. it was the year a female rugby player - at last - gained the sport's top honour. it was the 125th anniversary of suffrage, a year of celebration. but also a reminder that change does not come without hard work and frustration.... all year, we have watched as new zealand women have fought for their rights. and fought..... and fought.... from campaigning against sexual harassment in the media, to arguing for equal pay through the courts, to addressing our shameful domestic violence record at the united nations, women stood up and were counted. they raised their voices when others didn't want to hear. they were empowered in the face of adversity. they persisted despite knowing meaningful change would likely be a long time yet.

that persistence has led us to name women - all women - as our 2018 new zealanders of the year. #women #newzealandersoftheyear #metoo #payequity #equality #payparity. #un #nzwomen #nz #domesticviolence #womenssuffrage #one_womans_view #womeninmedicine

text:
i used to care about what people would think.
.
okay, i still do because iâ€™m human (duh) but it took an â€œinternet trollâ€ to make some unfriendly comment about my picture to realize that the sting lasted exactly .1 seconds and i was able to respectfully respond then bless and release it. there was a time that wouldâ€™ve brought on anxiety and pushed me so far back from the progress i made to care less of others opinions.
.
because let me tell you something sister. no one elseâ€™s opinion of how youâ€™re choosing to do life will get you to where you want to be. are you listening? their opinion on your job, parenting, physique, faith....matters zero%.
.
do you have big goals that youâ€™re burying and pushing down because youâ€™re scared to say them out loud for fear of what someone else will think? declare your business success! set that non-scale victory! go to the marriage conference! do the big scary thing if it is going to allow you to live the life you dream of!
.

.
babe - i know youâ€™re scared to leap. but trust the girl who said no for a year who wishes she had said yes all along.

i am outraged that the violence against women act (vawa) has officially expired due to the partial government shutdown.

since 1994 the vawa has protected victims of domestic violence and sexual assault and was the first federal legislation to recognize and address domestic violence as a serious crime. domestic violence and sexual assault programs funded by vawa will be cut off until the legislation is reauthorized.

as a domestic violence survivor, advocate and activist, i am utterly disappointed. you'll be hearing more from me on this topic. i'll never stop fighting for what's right.

#domesticviolenceawareness #sexualassaultawareness
#advocacyalert #advocacy 
#victimrights #metoo 
#stopviolenceagainstwomen
#timesup #vawa #nomore 
#thestillstandingalliance

text:
thinkÂ vogueÂ and the mind immediately conjures images of men and women dressed in designer clothes. the vogue women of the year 2018 awards was no different.however, the one lady that stood out in her crpf uniform was 28-year-old usha kiran.

this lady singham is the youngest female crpf officer to be a part of commando battalion for resolute action (cobra) and is currently serving the volatile region of bastar in chhattisgarh. during her training period, she requested her seniors to allow her to serve under the male battalion in an extreme left-wing infested state, or j&k, or north-east front areas. finally, she was given chhattisgarh region, bastar a district dreaded with maoist activities. also in her spare time, she helps the school going girls in their studies.

she is an inspiration to many and a role model for young tribal women in joining the armed forces.
sources: indiatimes & thebetterindia.com

text:
kita butuh uu yang akan membarier kita dari persoalan-persoalan kekerasan seksual terhadap perempuan, dan siapapun itu.

indonesia sedang darurat kekerasan seksual. berbagai kasus kekerasan seksual tidak mendapat ruang keadilan dimata hukum.  konstruksi berpikir yg timpang dan dominasi relasi kuasa menyebabkan superioritas patriarki masih menjamur dalam segala lini.

pun soal budaya konservatisme yang berjalan kelindan dengan budaya patriarki sedang sama-sama merawat stigma negatif bagi korban kekerasan seksual.

korban cenderung distigma sebagai pemicu atas persoalan yang dialami. padahal, korban butuh dampingan dan keadilan dimata hukum.

kita menginginkan negara ini, sadar hukum dan adil gender. segra sahkan ruu penghapusan kekerasan seksual !!! menangkan pancasila
wujudkan kesetaraan gender dan kesejahteraan sosial

tina turner bullock #swisssisters #lindorchocolate the pÃºca (irish for spirit/#ghost), pooka, phouka, phooka, phooca, puca or pÃºka is primarily a creature of celtic folklore.[1] considered to be bringers both of good and bad fortune, they could either help or hinder rural and marine communities. the pÃºca can have dark or white fur or hair. the creatures were said to be shape changers which could take the appearance of #horses, goats, cats, dogs, and #hares. they may also take a human form, which includes various animal features, such as ears or a tail.
the pÃºca has counterparts throughout the celtic cultures of #northwest europe. for instance, in welsh mythology it is named the pwca and in cornish the bucca.[2] in the channel islands, the pouque were said to be fairies who lived near ancient stones; in channel island french a cromlech, or prehistoric tomb, is referred to as a pouquelÃ©e or pouquelay(e); poulpiquet and polpegan are corresponding terms in #brittany.the origin of the name may have come from the #oldnorse term pook or puki, which refers to a "nature spirit". usage of the term in ireland, however, may predate the arrival of #norse settlers.[5] in germanic languages, such as#frisian or english, this became pucel, pook or #puck. the name of the pooka may also come from the irish word poc, meaning a male goat, a form the creature is often said to take.there are stories of some pÃºca being blood-thirsty and vampire-like creatures. other stories even say some are man-eating beings, hunting down, killing, and eating their victims.
morphology and physiology
according to legend, the pÃºca is a deft shapeshifter, capable of assuming a variety of terrifying or pleasing forms. it can take a human form, but will often have animal features, such as ears or a tail.[12] as an animal, the pÃºca will most commonly appear as a horse, cat,#rabbit, raven,#fox, wolf, goat, goblin, or dog. no matter what shape the pÃºca takes, its fur is almost always dark. it most commonly takes the form of a sleek black horse with a flowing mane and luminescent golden eyes.[13] (the manx glashtyn also takes on human form, but he usually betrays his horse's ears and is analogous to the each u

es curioso como un momento histÃ³rico puede empujar mucho mÃ¡s a un filme. la historia de una mujer, en apariencia dÃ©bil, que decide vengarse de sus abusadores es tan vieja como el propio cine. tÃ­tulos como 'a cruel picture', 'i spit on your grave', 'la Ãºltima casa a la izquierda' o 'demented' asÃ­ lo demuestran. de todas ellas bebe 'kill bill', la cinta de quentin tarantino. pero en plena explosiÃ³n del #metoo, 'revenge' toma un nuevo sentido.

text:
choose love daily. choose it for yourself & for others.
.
.
showing yourself love every single day will transform your life.
.
.
showing love to others every single day will transform your life.
.
.
if you are doing those 2 things, there's no way your life won't change. .
.
some ideas for yourself: daily meditation, choosing healthy food daily, working out daily, yoga daily, daily affirmations, reading positive books, prayer, taking a bath, relaxing, getting pampered, alone time, sleep, doing your hair & makeup. so so many more, that's a start!
.
.
some ideas for others: random acts of kindness to strangers, doing something you don't want to do but will to show another love, your significant others love language, calling an old friend, calling a grandparent or parent, bringing food to someone sick or new parent, buying a gift as a surprise, writing a letter or card for no reason. .
.

text:
#24speciesofcrane day 22

leucogeranus leucogeranus, leucogeranus leucogeranus, the siberian or snow crane. pictured above is likely the last specimen seen in north america as it perches in some sort of native #forage. 
the siberian crane migrates the furthest of any crane, each year finding their summer feeding grounds back in the ussr, where the western populations number less than 11, some counts suggest there are only four remaining cranes, dubbed the #fabfour. the cranes continue to be assassinated by hunters, fears that only three exist following entanglement with a japanese female are unconfirmed as yet. if thats not enough, there main food source are beatles, by some loose reference.

the snow goose call is normally described as a shrill #toyoya. some far eastern populations have translated this as "#toyota". eliyahu m goldratt asserts that the meticulous nest building techniques were copied exactly by taiichi ohno and eiji toyoda in their world leading production system, but herbie objects. 
the crane has always been a cultural leader in the area, the local shamans and shamanesses have been confirmed in many cases to be able to transform at will into these birds. really amazing stuff, exactly why we at #cranequarters started the #cranesarepeopletoo hashtag in the first place. 
some of the threats to the crane include so called #greenpower #hydro projects like the three rivers dam. other threats include hunting, agriculture and reindeer. further to this, farmers often shoot at the birds as they often eat the worms we require fore the biodynamic #veganfood we love.

why do the cranes not understand we are farming vegetables for their benefit, we dont want to revert to the #wrong ways of our ancestors and have to rely on meat and fish to grow healthy and strong. why cant they just join the #vegancrane cause and stop killing worms and fish?

#endtheextinction #creaseforpeace #fighttheman #metoo #endtheextinction #earthtoo #cranestoo #lgbqtc @peta @seashepherd #christmas #origami #vegetablepower #vegetable #vegancat #veganleopard
name: OG Crane Creaser

text: i won't elaborate on my past. but for decades i felt powerless, i felt that i was stuck with what was. my mother telling me "it's what women like you get in life.."(she was refering to my lack of attractiveness) it took three things in my life to strengthen my back, to force me forward. it was the past year that opened my eyes, woke me up. a year of acceptance(of good and bad) a year of growth, a year of realizing the power in my own hands, within me. two of those things were my daughter's. i -refused- to let them grow up in the world i had. now, i don't want someone out there waiting decades like i did to wake up to their personal power the control of their life, their acceptance of self! even if my (often glitter ridden) post help one person. i will be happy. i want to be the voice i didn't hear in my life! i want people to believe  in themselves!! ğŸŒ¹ğŸ’—ğŸŒ¹#selflove #selfcare #selfdiscovery #wellbeing #wellness #jusssayin #settingboundariesandfsu #thetruthturnsmeon #boundaries #nocontact #redflags #narcissist #narcissisticabuse #narcissism #metoo #abuse #crazymaking #emotionalabuse #toxicrelationships #survivor #gaslighting #toxicpeopleÂ  #mentalhealthawareness #domesticviolence #believewomen #ifmywoundswerevisible #dontlookback #narcissisticabusesurvivor #witchesofinstagram  #pagansofinstagram

text:
today was just one of those days. i've been doing a lot of reflecting and am really preparing myself for an end of year emotional cleanse/shedding where i hope to let go of a lot of internal stuff that is no longer serving me. this work is hard. but it's what makes me stronger and stronger every day. i bawled my eyes out today and once i'd had a good cry, i remembered this quote i'd found yesterday and it was kind of the answer i needed. i know what i need to let go of but yet the residual attachment issues i have from past trauma keeps me stuck longing for what i know just isn't good for me. at a brain level, i know i deserve better. i just need to bring the rest of me on board. what do you guys do to help yourselves really get that you do deserve better? â¤

message from chelsea miller: 
january 25-26, 2019, columbia university will be hosting the third annual her legacy conference and gala. after two days of workshops and panels ranging from "unlocking your leadership potential" to "redefining activism", attendees will end their weekend walking the red carpet at the her legacy gala. the gala will be an evening of live performances, awards, and special guests. tarana burke founder of the #metoo movement and recently named person of the year by time magazine was honored last year. over a dozen media platforms will be covering the weekend. â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”-
tickets start as low as $15 (food included). though centering the voices of women and girls of color, the weekend is open to everyone. (available on eventbrite) - link : https://www.eventbrite.com/e/her-legacy-conference-gala-2019-tickets-53576428540#tickets

text:
i am a recovering perfectionist.

its hard work. my mind still freaks when i feel i didnt measure up, or let someone down or i looked stupid. i panic because i'm afraid of abandonment and rejection. i'm self aware enough to know this about me, yet i still struggle.

i'm learning to calm down and accept the fact i'm not perfect, and i wont do everything right all the time. it's too much pressure to live trying to perform and be perfect in everything. my anxiety goes up, i getÂ back pain and lose my appetite. whew! gonna try and release some of this into the new year.

still a queen ğŸ‘‘âœŠ.

text: the year in illustration 2018. we call on illustrators late at night, in the early morning and on deadline. the subjects are complex: #metoo, the immigration debate, climate change. we ask them to address these topics with sensitivity, wit and feeling â€” to add fresh perspective and avoid clichÃ©. also, â€œcan you send a sketch in a few hours?â€ we call on them because, at a time when the news cycle can feel relentless and overwhelming, these images make a different kind of impact: conveying emotion, creating space for thought, adding depth to subjects that may feel at once both too complex and overly familiar. from the thousands of illustrations that appeared in print and online in the new york times this year, here are some of the most notable: the ones that surprised us, that made us feel something, that made us laugh â€” the ones that made us pause a moment longer than we might have on a busy day in 2018. click the link in our bio for some of the most notable illustrations seen on our pages this year. above, illustrations by @gabalca, @moniiqwa, @armandoveve, @till_lauer. #art #illustration #2018 #images

text:
"the pit, snakes, scorpions and forgiveness" will be our teaching this sunday for our last gathering of 2018. in order to fully move forward into a new year, we need to learn to find healing of our past, forgive those who have brought us harm and even harder learn to forgive ourselves. sometimes it's easier to extend grace to someone else more than it is to yourself. have you been there? .
.

are you tired of viewing your present and your future through the filter and lens of your past hurt, pain, regret and dissapointments? who is that person you carry around even though they aren't there? what is that thing, that you just can't seem to get past? do you long for the forgiveness of god? there is freedom from unforgiveness, bitterness, resentment, regret, or self hatred. jesus wants to kick down every wall we've built and bring us out into the freedom of wide and open spaces mentally and spiritually. .
.
.

text:
do you have a favourite dress that kate has worn? here are my 3 favourite dresses she wore in 2018! all 3 were designed by jenny packham (and one of kate's top go-to designers!)
.
1) kate attended the baftas during the #metoo movement. as a royal, she isn't allowed to make a political statement (the women who attended all wore black) but i think she still respected the movement in choosing a gorgeous dark forest green gown!
.
2) kate rewore a stunning turquoise gown from 2012 to the tusk trust awards, this is my personal favourite dress she has ever worn, aside from her wedding dress!!
.
3) kate donned a pale ice blue gown at the diplomatic corps review, it gave me some frozen/elsa vibes and i thought it was a stunning gown!

the year in illustration 2018. we call on illustrators late at night, in the early morning and on deadline. the subjects are complex: #metoo, the immigration debate, climate change. we ask them to address these topics with sensitivity, wit and feeling â€” to add fresh perspective and avoid clichÃ©. also, â€œcan you send a sketch in a few hours?â€ we call on them because, at a time when the news cycle can feel relentless and overwhelming, these images make a different kind of impact: conveying emotion, creating space for thought, adding depth to subjects that may feel at once both too complex and overly familiar. from the thousands of illustrations that appeared in print and online in the new york times this year, here are some of the most notable: the ones that surprised us, that made us feel something, that made us laugh â€” the ones that made us pause a moment longer than we might have on a busy day in 2018. click the link in our bio for some of the most notable illustrations seen on our pages this year. above, illustrations by @gabalca, @moniiqwa, @armandoveve, @till_lauer. #art #illustration #2018 #images

text:
and some days, you find yourself curled up in a ball on the kitchen floor.
sobbing.
acknowledging the pain.
and releasing it.
this is real life.
itâ€™s not to be glamorized, or judged, or scripted for a 1x1 digital square. i never promised to be anything but myself on this platform. to show you the truest version of me, in all forms. the good, the messy, and the not-so-perfect sides of me.
â€¢
you see, silencing the messy parts of us is an act of isolation. at its core silence is the antithesis of compassionâ€”which is the one thing we need for healing, integrating human connection and creating lasting change in this world.
â€¢
how can we connect when weâ€™re silent? in a time when weâ€™re more â€œconnectedâ€ than ever, weâ€™re more isolated than everâ€”as loneliness has reached â€œepidemic levels.â€ according to recent national studies: 1 in 4 americans feel like no one trully knows them & generation z is now the â€œloneliest generationâ€ in the history of the our country, with 70% feeling like no one knows the real them.
â€¢
part of me didnâ€™t want to share this photo. what will people say, what will people think?
but...
what if...
what if this photo sets people free?
what if this photo gives someone else the permission theyâ€™ve been searching for to walk in their imperfect truth?
â€¢
sending love to anyone feeling like theyâ€™re going it alone. i promise you, thereâ€™s a world thatâ€™s desperate for the real you. thatâ€™s desperate for your voice. we need it to heal, to connect, to change.
â€¢
we need youâ€”all of the messy-broken-fucked up-beautiful parts of you.

text:
#washington: the trump administration announced on friday a plan designed to make it easier for coal-fired power plants, after nearly a decade of restrictions, to once again release into the atmosphere mercury and other pollutants linked to developmental disorders and respiratory illnesses.

the limits on mercury, set in 2011, were the first federal standards to restrict some of the most hazardous pollutants emitted by coal plants and were considered one of former president barack obamaâ€™s signature environmental achievements. since then, scientists have said, mercury pollution from power plants has declined more than 80 percent nationwide.

president trumpâ€™s new proposal does not repeal the regulation, known as the mercury and air toxics standards, but it would lay the groundwork for doing so by weakening a key legal justification for the measure. the long-term impact would be significant: it would weaken the ability of the e.p.a. to impose new regulations in the future by adjusting the way the agency measures the benefits of curbing pollutants, giving less weight to the potential health gains.â€

text:
#romjulroar day 3: in 2017 i spoke publicly about me rape for the first time. i was terrified. then, nothing bad happened. then, other women shared their experiences with me. â€¢
my vulnerability doesn't make me weak. it belies the strength required to survive. if some perceive me as less-than, or think i should keep it to myself, that's on them. my trauma is not laundry to be washed or luggage to carry. it's part of my experience and enhances my ability to empathize with, and in turn serve, others.
â€¢
imma serve by leading, and by sharing my vulnerability moarrrrrr in 2019.
â€¢

text:
celebrating screen star tayo sobola

multi talented actress, model, video vixen, presenter and producer. toya sobola  aka sotayo gaga was definitely born for the cameras.

although known in the yoruba film industry, the graduate of sociology from olabisi onabanjo university, ogun state started out featuring in english language movies.

the actress who has featured in many movies including: idakeji ife, egan, corper jide, bella, arewa onijogbon and others is known for the film, arewa onijogbonÂ (2012). sobolaÂ attended olabisi onabanjo university where she bagged  a degree in public administration and a diploma in law from lagos state university.

the actress is said to have a multi million naira production studio.

in 2015, she won city peopleâ€™s entertainment awards for best new yoruba actress of the year and was nominated in another category for most promising actress of the year.

happy 33rd birthday sotayo gaga!

text:
a bishop sent me a message saying l should stop taking about sexual violence since god has helped me,now l am married(in his words) he went as far as advising me  not to bring shame on the man who married me. in his words the man did me a great favor. 
this is my response, sir with all due respect l will not stop talking. i will continue to lend my voice ,l will continue to speak out  against rape ,molestation,incest or any form of sexual violence until something is done. i am a christian girl who is not ashamed to speak out. 
our dear ochanya died after being violated sexually for years by father and son ğŸ˜­ğŸ˜­ and some people still think talking about this does not make sense? how many more innocent children will die before we know there is an emergency? most sexual violence cases are perpetrated by people the victims know. because of society's shame,stigma and judgement most survivors never speak. the number of survivors who have spoken is nothing compared to the ones who have never spoken about their abuse. we will not keep quiet. 
sexual violence can have harmful and lasting consequences for the victims,families, communities.  sexual violence victimisation is associated with several health risk behaviour. the effects can have psychological,emotional,and physical effects on a survivor. the effects are not easy to deal,it can take a life time to heal. with the right help and support survivors can be managed.

sexual violence is not a joke,it should never be trivialised.  we will not be silenced. our voice,our power.... to everyone who has survived, l salute you big time. i salute your courage. i salute your strength. we survived the abuse,we will definitely survive the recovery . our lives matter. 
#metoomovement #metoo #notoviolenceagainstwomen #nigerianfeminist #irememberabuse #unmutted #awakening

text:
"the pit, snakes, scorpions and forgiveness" will be our teaching this sunday for our last gathering of 2018. in order to fully move forward into a new year, we need to learn to find healing of our past, forgive those who have brought us harm and even harder learn to forgive ourselves. sometimes it's easier to extend grace to someone else more than it is to yourself. have you been there? .
.

are you tired of viewing your present and your future through the filter and lens of your past hurt, pain, regret and dissapointments? who is that person you carry around even though they aren't there? what is that thing, that you just can't seem to get past? do you long for the forgiveness of god? there is freedom from unforgiveness, bitterness, resentment, regret, or self hatred. jesus wants to kick down every wall we've built and bring us out into the freedom of wide and open spaces mentally and spiritually. .
.
.
the fringe church | sundays 10am
www.thefringehamilton.com
105 n. 2nd street (ymca)
hamilton, ohio 45011
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

remember the scene of the black white supremacists on dave chapelle. when he took off his hood and revealed himself as a black man, the dudes head blew up.

this isn't racism, this is programming and whites have been lied to and deceived just like the blacks have. we are all enemies of satan, so he plays all of us. we're all rats in the maze.

text:
there can be an unspoken conspiracy in community-i certainly used to be a part of this and it goes something like this-
letâ€™s not demand much of ourselves.  or each other.  or of life.  and when it doesnâ€™t go the way we want to to, letâ€™s complain about it and everyone else.  for months. 
thereâ€™s another option 
if i am like the 5 people i spend the most time with, iâ€™m very careful of who i allow into my life. 
what am i up to?
what are they up to?
what am i healing?
what are they healing?
do i have a mentor i trust?
do they?
if i start to go off course are these the people i trust to tell me iâ€™m off?
are these the people i want to celebrate with?

for the first time in my life those around me are absolutely those people.  and it all started with an intention for this year of â€œa community that is loving, nurturing and freeâ€

because when we heal we heal generations before and after us, as well as the ripple affect around us. 
who are your people? 
what are your intentions for 2019?

if you need some help with intentions, are ready to heal and ignite the fire, letâ€™s talk.  letâ€™s heal this one friend group at a time ğŸ˜Šâ¤ï¸ğŸŒˆğŸ’—ğŸ’•ğŸ„

this year saw the highest estimated turnout for midterms in more than 100 years. there were a bunch of positive firsts, like the first muslim women and first native american women elected to congress, the first openly gay man elected as governor, among others. more congresswomen were elected than ever before. but florida still doesnâ€™t understand elections.
ğŸ¤¦â€â™‚ï¸ then there was brett kavanaugh, president @realdonaldtrumpâ€™s second addition to the supreme court after justice kennedy put in his notice. kavanaugh was accused by professor dr. christine blasey ford of sexually assaulting her decades ago. other women came forward with stories, too. kavanaugh denies them all. there were hearings. and protests. and lots and lots of opinions. some thought he deserved the benefit of the doubt. others felt we should #believewomen. a lot of people were reminded of anita hill. nonetheless, kavanaugh got the job.

text:
kwanzaa  day 3: ujima (collective work and responsibility) to build and maintain our community together and make our brothers' and sisters' problems our problems, and to solve them together.

scriptures for reflection:
nehemiah 2:17-18 (nrsv)
1 corinthians 12:21-25 (nrsv)

if the first principle dealt with the concept of unity, then the third one expands the conversation to include work and responsibility, not as individuals but as a collective. given the state of our communities, we should take this moment to realize that like the people of israel during nehemiah's time we must not only fight off external threats, we must also work internally to increase our strength. to give this a concrete example, we need to be vigilant about fighting for justice and restoration for those impacted by the #metoo movement just as we are about the  #blacklivesmatter movement. we need to fight for the rights of black people against white supremacy as well as challenge ourselves to not repeat the behaviors of our oppressors when it comes to up holding patriarchal systems or denying the rights and humanity of our lgbtq family. it really is either we all get free or nobody is free... and the freedom takes work, it's not cheap and it requires all of us to do our part, in our lanes as god has called us to do. 
ujima also reminds us not to get so caught up in our roles and statues. the late prophet frantz fanon once spoke to this in his book "wretched of the earth" when he said "for when the troops come we will either all be saved or all be captured; in such a context, the "every man for himself concept, the atheist's form of salvation, is prohibited.*" your titles, statuses, class affiliation etc won't save you. it may offer some small privilege but it will not save you. we truly are in this fight together. this is bore out in the scripture from 1 corinthians. all parts of the body make up the whole and when working together, so much more is achieved. no part is greater than the whole and it is all of our responsibility to fight the good fight in whatever venue or role we can. 
can we work together so we can all be free? 
pastor t

text: jordan is a six-year-old boy who loves basketball, dancing and superheroes. jordan came to the new york center for children after he disclosed that his uncle sexually abused him. when jordan began therapy at nycc, he suffered from severe trauma. he often cried, had tantrums, reported daily nightmares and flashbacks. through the power of play therapy and the use of superheroes, jordan was able to talk about the abuse he experienced in a safe space. therapy helped jordan make sense of his abuse and begin healing. for jordan, therapy has been an incredible gift. this holiday season, we invite you to give a child who has experienced abuse a gift that will last a lifetime: the gift of therapy. to donate, read more about jordan and how your support can help children like him heal and succeed, please visit the link on bio. ğŸ ğŸ’

this canada wide anti-sexual violence in the restaurant industry donation page has reached significant amounts and itâ€™s worth noticing because itâ€™s just going to get bigger.  the movement is growing and will spread over the next months to hold more people accountable as well as supporting the causes and organizations that support victims of sexual violence.  donate today to help them reach their goals and stay tuned for more coming soon. 
this fundraiser (https://fundly.com/hospitality-industry-standing-with-survivors) is endorsed by members of the food and wine industries in toronto/prince edward county, as well as a number of canadian celebrity food personalities like jen agg, matty matheson, joe beef, ivy knight. 
the fundraiser was started after the survivor accounts  of rape and sexual violence were revealed about norman hardie who is the founder and operator of norman hardie wines.  i am in constant contact with victims and with the organizers of this fundraiser to help anyway i can.  it would be amazing if some ottawa restaurant owners and businesses came onboard to help with the cause.  the #metoo movement is becoming a real thing now and you wonâ€™t be able to ignore it.  do not end up in the cross hairs when people start questioning your silence when it comes to addressing sexual misbehaviour in the food world.  follow for more info and support -> @dandelioninitiative @mmmarywood 
also tagging the following organizations and people who have been working on similar initiatives in ottawa -> @octevaw @sascottawa @baileyreid85 @badandbitchypod #ordersup #metoo #timesup

text: 2018 had the highest highs. (legit one if my best years ever.) and it marked the year that i was raped for the 6th time. didn't realize how healing this journey of health has been for all aspects of my life. reading "not that bad" edited by roxane gay and the "grown-woman theology" chapter of "eloquent rage" by brittany c. cooper broke me and built me up. advocating for myself in all ways taught me how to love myself. taking care of my body forced me to confront my fat shaming ways and internalized guilt of the pain my body held. my life looks very different than it did last year. i own my body and sexuality in a way i haven't before. require my partners to attend to my needs fully or bounce. use lingerie as a tool of healing and liberation. am i grateful for my rape? fuck no. am i reframing what the event meant in my life? abso-fucking-lutely. #metoo #bralettesasshirtsforeva #selfcareerryday

text_retweet:
heads held high, survivors! get ready to smash those pearls (unless they were gifted) or put on that pantsuit!

we're entering 2019 unashamed and with rejuvenated spirits and the strength to impact massive change. it's time we started using our powerful voices to speak out against sexual violence and abuse. 
in a world where 1 in 4 (probably more like 1 in 3) will experience some variation of sexual violence/abuse/assault, it's important that we fight as hard as we can to protect each other.

personally, i'm dedicating this year to learning how to change society's view of sexual violence/abuse, teaching prevention, supporting other survivors, partnering with other survivor communities, and being more bold in my advocacy. 
what are you going to do this year to help fight sexual violence? share in the comments or give helpful suggestions to other readers!

text:
i once wanted to take a road trip to the cabins in tennessee with a black chick. i planned to do some fishing and hunting. i vet women this way if i view them as relationship material. obviously this is before i was mgtow. i vet them on quite a few things but these are common ones.

1. her ability to get down and dirty in nature without complaining. use her hands, fish effectively, clean the fish. kick her shoes off and get dirty.

2. put her on the motorcycle with me and ride like hell is chasing me. i expect her to freak out but i want to gauge her reaction, because it's a direct correlation of her trust for me. getting out of her comfort zone is a sign of trust.

3. i grab the rifle go to a hunting cabin and test her marksmenship skills. if road trip isn't feasible go to the gun range.

it was a vacation/shit-test/evaluation to see if she was worth investing in. this is to see if she is able to live off the land and survive in nature for when the shtf.

this chick told me, can we fly there instead cuz i already did the whole road trip thing plenty of times with my ex. so before i could even make the trip to vet her she eliminated herself.

if a woman has done something or been somewhere with a previous guy, it would behoove of her to accept the opportunity because every new person brings about a new experience.

lmagine a chick doesn't want to go to amsterdam anymore because she has been many times with an ex. if you're a man that has always wanted to go to amsterdam and the chick you love doesn't want to share the moment with you, how would you feel?

men like to make their women happy. like when you get your kids a toy they always wanted, to see the joy in their face. so imagine getting a kid the same gift 10 years in a row, they won't have the same joy as the first time.

a mgtow tuber wanted to buy a home with his fiance. she said let's just move into my place. they both had homes but he wanted to create new memories, she was already attached to her home.

one very common one is when a man marries a single mother. since she already has kids she may tell him she doesn't want more, denying him the opportunity to create his legacy through a woman he loves.

text:
5 years ago i got this tattoo.  at the time it was 6 months since i had been raped.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
i was holding my breath waiting for january 1 to come. i wanted to be in a new year where i hadn't been raped. when i could say it happened "last year" and not "earlier this year."â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
i wanted to be out of 2013 as fast as possible.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
but, i also wanted a mindset to take with me on my journey into the future as i continued to pursue healing.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
this tattoo is a reminder of hope in the promise that light always conquers darkness, and a reminder to walk alongside others to help them in their journey thru life's hardships.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
more specifically for me, and for anyone else who believes in heaven, it is a reminder that the true "infinity" is one day all pain and suffering in this world will be done. a reminder that pain and injustice won't have the final word.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
and also the reminder that we aren't there yet, and therefore i want to do all i can to help others during this time where so much pain and injustice exists in this world.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
everything i am doing with restoring heart is sprung from that desire to help people - whatever their hardship. to help you move forward in the midst of fear - one brave baby step at a time, like i did.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
facing what happened to me and working through it was the most difficult thing of my entire life, but eventually, i reached a point where i no longer felt imprisoned by what happened to me.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
also, by fighting for myself, i learned to truly love and value myself.  and i want that same thing for you!â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
i hope each week's episode of the restoring heart podcast is helping you wherever you find yourself in life.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
for #metoo survivors, i look forward to opening haven in late january. it will be an online space with videos and a community with other survivors for you to walk alongside with. stay tuned. <3â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
